So here are some of the most important protocols and what they do ↓

@Kinetiq_xyz | Liquid staking. Stake HYPE, receive kHYPE, use it across DeFi.

@hyperlendx | Lending protocol. Supply assets, earn interest, borrow against collateral.

@Morpho | Permissionless lending infrastructure for isolated markets and automated vaults.

@ValantisLabs | Builds stHYPE liquid staking and specialized liquidity products for the ecosystem.

@felixprotocol | Borrow stablecoins against HYPE and other assets, access Morpho-based lending markets.

@prjx_hl | HyperEVM spot DEX. Swap tokens and LPs to earn trading fees.

@hyperbeat | Automated yield vaults, liquid staking, payments, and onchain banking in one platform.

@DeriveXYZ | Onchain options platform. Trade options, use HYPE as collateral.

@ryskfinance | Options-based yield. Earn premiums by selling covered calls.

@pendle_fi | Yield trading. Lock in fixed returns or speculate on future yield changes.

@unitxyz | Asset tokenization layer that brings BTC, ETH, SOL into Hyperliquid for trading and DeFi.

@eulerfinance | Modular lending infrastructure with configurable markets and vaults on HyperEVM.

Which ones are you using lately?

